name: Frank A. CARTER, Jr., Chief Disciplinary Counsel v. Stephen R. WALSH

parties: Frank A. CARTER, Jr., Chief Disciplinary Counsel v. Stephen R. WALSH.

opinions.text:
ORDER
The respondent’s motion requesting permission to resign as a member of the Bar of this State is granted.
WEISBERGER, J., did not participate.

attorneys: Charles H. McLaughlin, Providence, for respondent.
casebody.head_matter:
Frank A. CARTER, Jr., Chief Disciplinary Counsel v. Stephen R. WALSH.
No. 79-227-M.P.
Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
May 29, 1980.
Frank A. Carter, pro se.
Charles H. McLaughlin, Providence, for respondent.
